"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-2043220-olympic-legend-shelly-ann-fraser-pryce\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Olympic icon Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce amusingly outclassed her competitors during a parents' race at sports day.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 38, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The eight-timeOlympicmedallist demonstrated her fierce competitive spirit by ruthlessly destroying the other mums.\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce boasts two Olympic gold medals in the 100m from the 2008 Beijing games and London 2012, along with a third gold in the 4x100m relay from Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 390, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 294, \"end\": 306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9996518383636257, \"rank\": 0.0003482763772126032, \"text\": \"2008 Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 317, \"end\": 328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999976357685, \"rank\": 2.3640324851288602e-09, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 379, \"end\": 384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.96810184654104, \"rank\": 0.031565233161163574, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Social media footage showed the Jamaican sprinter taking the event seriously, even warming up on the start line of the uneven grass track.\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 424, \"end\": 432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9992678570655015, \"rank\": 0.0007326793603822245, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce was seen stretching her legs with a high-knees run while the other parents congregated nearby.\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A second video provided an aerial view of the race, with the 38-year-old starting in the middle lane.\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her reaction time proved to be as sharp as ever, as she was the first off the line in the 100m.\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just a few metres into the race, she had already established a clear lead and continued to distance herself from the other parents.\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 968, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the video progressed, Fraser-Pryce crossed the finish line around four seconds faster than the other parents, so fast that the video struggled to keep her in frame.\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce is the third fastest woman in history, having set a personal best of 10.60, and is widely regarded as the greatest female sprinter of all time, having won more sprint titles than any other woman in history.\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1357, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Enthralled fans flocked to social media to gush over the sensational clip, with one user exclaiming: \\\"S